               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa śǝnä fǝṭrat "Book of the Beauty of Creation" (fols. 3r-98v).
                     In Amharic (cp. EMML no. 1392)
 I-1) Introduction: a treatise on creation
                     (fols. 3r-5v)
 I-2) Sunday (fols. 6r-24r)
 I-3) Monday (fols.
                     24r-26v)
 I-4) Tuesday (fols. 26v-34r)
 I-5) Wednesday (fols.
                     34r-44r)
 I-6) Thursday (fols. 44r-48r)
 I-7) Friday (fols.
                     48r-57r)
 I-8) Saturday (fol. 57r)
 I-9) Symbolic interpretation of the
                     creation (fols. 57v-70v)
 I-10) Creation of Eve (fols. 70v-98v) 
 II)
                     ʾAmmǝstu ʾaʿmāda mǝśṭir "The Five Pillars of Mystery" (fols. 99r-144v)
                     II-1) Introduction (fols. 99r-103r)
 II-2) Mǝśṭira Śǝllāse “Mystery of the
                     Trinity” (fol. 103r)
 II-3) Mǝśṭira śǝggāwe “Mystery of the Incarnation”
                     (fol. 103r)
 II-4) Mǝśṭira ṭǝmqat “Mystery of Baptism” (fol. 103v)
                     II-5) Mǝśṭira qʷǝrbān “Mystery of the Eucharist” (fols. 103v-104r)
 II-6)
                     Mǝśṭira tǝnśāʾe mutān “Mystery of the Resurrection of the Dead” (fol.
                     104r)
 II-7) Symbolic interpretation of words Five, Pillar, and Mystery
                     (fols. 104r-110v)
 II-8) Mǝgbarat “Good Deeds” (fols. 110v-121r) (cp. EMML
                     no. 1315 2)(19))
 II-9) Hāymānot kä-mǝgbar “Faith and Good Deed” (fols.
                     121r-132v)
 II-10) Ṣādǝqān “The Righteous Ones” (fols. 132v-142v)
                     II-11) Adam’s Faith (fols. 142v-144v).</summary>
